A federal judge allowed Tyco International Ltd. shareholders to proceed with a class action lawsuit against the company.
The lawsuit seeks damages for fraud and corporate looting.
Former executives Kozlowski and Swartz are accused of stealing millions from Tyco.
Prosecutors allege they hid bonuses and inflated stock prices.
The retrial focuses on their lavish spending and deception.
Defense lawyers argue the compensation was justified.
The trial highlights corporate scandals and criminal enforcement.
Prosecutors emphasize the illegal self-awarding of bonuses.
The defense aims to separate the roles of the accused executives.
The jury must evaluate the evidence against each man individually.
